extends /_layouts/_index.pug

block content
  article.content-artice
    section.subheader
      div.messagetop
      div.submessage
        p The Ten-Year Capital Strategy defines the City of New York&#8217;s vision to improve our infrastructure, buildings, and neighborhoods across the five boroughs. It reflects each City agency's long-term goals, defines our citywide investment priorities, and is guided by two principles:
        p.more-info
          a(href='/principle_advance_neighborhood_based_capital_planning.html') 1. Advance neighborhood-based capital planning
        p.more-info
          a(href='/principle_maintain_new_york_citys_financial_responsibility.html') 2. Maintain New York City's financial responsibility
        p.more-info
          a(href='/principle_planning_for_growth.html') 3. Advance neighborhood-based capital planning
        p.more-info
          a(href='/principle_maintain_new_york_citys_financial_responsibility.html') 4. Maintain New York City's financial responsibility
    article.content-body.index-body
      div.grid-1
        span &nbsp;
      section#section-1.partial-page
        h2 NYC&#8217;s Capital Strategy will catalyze real progress across six investment priorities.
        p.
          New Yorkers can expect visible improvements in schools, transit, parks, and more. Below are just some of the outcomes we&#8217;re working toward.

      section#section-2.full-page
        div.improvements
          div.improvement
            a(href="/priority_maintain_our_infrastructure.html")
              div.top-half.improvements-buildings
              div.bottom-half.top-margin
                p.more-info Priority 1: Maintain and modernize our infrastructure to ensure a state of good repair
                h3.below <span class="title-highlight"> Expanding our drinking water delivery  </span> systems through City Water Tunnel #3
          div.improvement
            a(href="/priority_support_growth_and_preserve_affordability.html")
              div.top-half.improvements-parks
              div.bottom-half
                p.more-info Priority 2: Support growth and preserve affordability in our diverse neighborhoods
                h3 <span class="title-highlight">Building and preserving affordable </span> housing for the New Yorkers who need it the most
          div.improvement
            a(href="/priority_expand_access_to_education_and_economic_opportunity.html")
              div.top-half.improvements-schools
              div.bottom-half
                p.more-info Priority 3: Expand access to education and economic opportunity
                h3.below <span class="title-highlight">Improving accessibility in our </span> public school buildings to ensure all children have access to quality education
          div.improvement
            a(href="/priority_revitalize_and_protect_our_waterfront_across_all_five_boroughs.html")
              div.top-half.improvements-paths
              div.bottom-half
                p.more-info Priority 4: Address citywide resiliency goals, restore and protect our waterfront 
                h3 <span class="title-highlight"> Protecting lower manhattan waterfront</span> from future storms and sea level rise
          div.improvement
            a(href="/priority_build_stronger_connections_between_our_communities.html")
              div.top-half.improvements-ferries
              div.bottom-half
                p.more-info Priority 5: Build stronger connections between our communities
                h3 <span class="title-highlight">Closing the gaps on a 32 mile greenway</span> along the Manhttan waterfront
          div.improvement
            a(href="/priority_promote_the_health_and_safety_of_all_new_yorkers.html")
              div.top-half.improvements-shelters
              div.bottom-half
                p.more-info Priority 6: Promote the health and safety of all New Yorkers
                h3 <span class="title-highlight">Improving street and pedestrian safety</span> through Vision Zero initiatives
          div.clear

        p.more-info
          a(href='/priority_maintain_our_infrastructure.html') Learn more about our six priorities

